Enum Axis

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<Axis>
      • us.ihmc.euclid.Axis
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Axis>, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple3D.interfaces.Tuple3DReadOnly, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple3D.interfaces.Vector3DReadOnly

    public enum Axis
extends java.lang.Enum<Axis>
implements us.ihmc.euclid.tuple3D.interfaces.Vector3DReadOnly
    Axis can be used to provide a simple and readable way to refer the three main axes of a coordinate system.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      X
      The x-axis is usually associated with the forward direction.
      Y
      The y-axis is usually associated with the direction pointing to the left of the forward direction and is horizontal.
      Z
      The z-axis is usually associated with the vertical direction, parallel to the gravity vector but pointing the opposite direction.
